						<summary>

						<p>On a fourth pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 30: 936-37 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription records the gift of 90 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp to the deity with one <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee daily, by the measure <hi rend="italic">Tirumaṟaikkāḍaṉ.</hi> </p>						

